results.definition: emotional or moral sensitivity (especially in relation to personal principles or dignity)
examples: the remark hurt his feelings

results.definition: the experiencing of affective and emotional states
examples: she had a feeling of euphoria
he had terrible feelings of guilt
I disliked him and the feeling was mutual

results.definition: a vague idea in which some confidence is placed
examples: his impression of her was favorable
what are your feelings about the crisis?
it strengthened my belief in his sincerity
I had a feeling that she was lying

results.definition: the general atmosphere of a place or situation and the effect that it has on people
examples: the feel of the city excited him
a clergyman improved the tone of the meeting
it had the smell of treason

results.definition: a physical sensation that you experience
examples: he had a queasy feeling
I had a strange feeling in my leg
he lost all feeling in his arm

results.definition: the sensation produced by pressure receptors in the skin
examples: she likes the touch of silk on her skin
the surface had a greasy feeling

results.definition: an intuitive understanding of something
examples: he had a great feeling for music

results.definition: undergo an emotional sensation or be in a particular state of mind
examples: She felt resentful
He felt regret

results.definition: come to believe on the basis of emotion, intuitions, or indefinite grounds
examples: I feel that he doesn't like me
I find him to be obnoxious
I found the movie rather entertaining

results.definition: perceive by a physical sensation, e.g., coming from the skin or muscles
examples: He felt the wind
She felt an object brushing her arm
He felt his flesh crawl
She felt the heat when she got out of the car

results.definition: be conscious of a physical, mental, or emotional state
examples: My cold is gone--I feel fine today
She felt tired after the long hike
She felt sad after her loss

results.definition: have a feeling or perception about oneself in reaction to someone's behavior or attitude
examples: She felt small and insignificant
You make me feel naked
I made the students feel different about themselves

results.definition: undergo passive experience of:"We felt the effects of inflation"
examples: her fingers felt their way through the string quartet
she felt his contempt of her

results.definition: be felt or perceived in a certain way
examples: The ground feels shaky
The sheets feel soft

results.definition: grope or feel in search of something
examples: He felt for his wallet

results.definition: examine by touch
examples: Feel this soft cloth!
The customer fingered the sweater

results.definition: examine (a body part) by palpation
examples: The nurse palpated the patient's stomach
The runner felt her pulse

results.definition: find by testing or cautious exploration
examples: He felt his way around the dark room

results.definition: produce a certain impression
examples: It feels nice to be home again

results.definition: pass one's hands over the sexual organs of
examples: He felt the girl in the movie theater
